You are helping build CENTRAL, a church communication app for college ministry.

Tech stack: Next.js 16, Supabase, Tailwind CSS, shadcn/ui, TypeScript.

Project structure follows Next.js App Router conventions.
Supabase client is in lib/supabase.ts.
Environment variables are in .env.local.

Roles: Visitor, Member, Leader, Admin.

Key features being built:
- Personalized chat home (members only see their assigned chats)
- Church Chats (leader managed) and My Chats (private, member created)
- Announcements feed with RSVP
- Member directory
- Customizable profile with prayer requests and bible verse

Always use TypeScript. Always use Tailwind for styling. Use shadcn/ui components where possible. Keep components small and focused. Use Supabase for all database and auth operations.